ntal traditions, providing an intimate glimpse into what was unique about Byrd and his music. Elegantly written, with the particular brilliance for which Brett was known, this book opens a fascinating window onto one of the most fruitful periods of English musical history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aComposerszEngland. 0aMusiczEnglandy16th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  acatholic composers.  aclassical composer.  acourt composer.  afamous editor.  afamous historian.  agradualia.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ainstrumental.  amagnum opus.  amusic appreciation.  amusic history.  amusical tradition.  amusicians.  anobility.  apaston manuscripts.  apersonal essays.  apoetry and poets.  aprotestant and catholics.  aretrospective.  around table paper.  aroyalty.  asacred music.  asingers.  aspiritual.  atheatre.  atudor era music.  auntimely death.1 aKerman, Joseph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoroney, Davitt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093283840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932838423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932838/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles